OL,7,FSpeaking with ITV in 2000, Foden said:
OL,8,F"It seems to me that people would much
OL,9,Frather suspend teachers and conduct an
OL,10,Finvestigation afterwards, even if
OL,11,Fthere is no evidence a child is at
OL,12,Fsignificant risk, to watch their own
OL,13,Fbacks and unfortunately it's the
OL,14,Fteacher that suffers."
OL,16,FFollowing Foden's trial, Judge Rhys
OL,17,FRowlands criticised Gwynedd Council
OL,18,Ffor not investigating concerns about
OL,19,FFoden meeting girls alone as far back
OL,20,Fas 2019.
